cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new approach to value function approximation using a combination of reinforcement learning and subspace identification. This makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Bellman recursion, which is commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper uses statistical analysis to prove the consistency of the proposed algorithm, which suggests a connection to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
